cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for learning features from 3D shapes and representing them in a single-view image. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses a convolutional neural network for feature learning, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with unsupervised learning, which is a sub-topic of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with shape datasets, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper uses a latent space representation for object recognition, which is a sub-topic of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
